<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Terms and Conditions - Luxury Hotel Group</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/terms.css">
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <div class="nav-container">
            <h1>Luxury Hotel Group</h1>
            <div class="nav-links">
                <a href="/home">Home</a>
                <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
                <a href="/contact">Privacy</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <main>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>
            
            <section>
                <h2>1. Booking and Reservations</h2>
                <p>All reservations are subject to availability and confirmation. A valid credit card is required to secure your booking.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>2. Check-in and Check-out</h2>
                <p>Check-in time is from 3:00 PM, and check-out time is until 11:00 AM. Early check-in and late check-out may be available upon request.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>3. Cancellation Policy</h2>
                <p>Cancellations must be made at least 48 hours prior to arrival to avoid charges. Different rates may have different cancellation policies.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>4. Payment Terms</h2>
                <p>We accept major credit cards. Full payment is required at check-out unless otherwise specified.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>5. Property Rules</h2>
                <p>Guests are expected to maintain appropriate noise levels and respect other guests. Smoking is prohibited in all indoor areas.</p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Luxury Hotel Group. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        // JavaScript to load other documents using Node.js server
        document.querySelectorAll('a[data-page]').forEach(link => {
            link.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                fetch(this.getAttribute('data-page'))
                    .then(response => response.text())
                    .then(html => {
                        document.open();
                        document.write(html);
                        document.close();
                    })
                    .catch(error => console.error('Error loading document:', error));
            });
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>